WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:09.500
As Design Lead, I developed Testamentus.org, a Bible reader focused on extreme performance and accessibility.

00:09.500 --> 00:19.500
Using Lean UX methodology, I prioritized continuous learning and rapid validation to create an experience free of ads and distractions.

00:19.500 --> 00:28.500
The information architecture was designed to ensure that any content can be accessed in a maximum of three clicks, optimizing the user flow.

00:28.500 --> 00:37.500
The search engine, developed in PHP and MySQL, processes instant results, making it easier to locate specific verses and chapters.

00:37.500 --> 00:47.500
To ensure inclusion for all users, I also implemented a robust accessibility menu in compliance with WCAG AA standards.

00:47.500 --> 00:56.500
The system allows for dynamic adjustment of typography, spacing, and contrast, reducing visual fatigue during prolonged reading.

00:56.500 --> 01:08.500
I also facilitated a unique sharing feature where users can highlight and generate verse images for social media without needing to log in, saved locally on the device.

01:08.500 --> 01:18.500
The entire interface is mobile-first and responsive, adapting fluidly across devices to serve the 65% of users who access via mobile.

01:18.500 --> 01:28.500
Technical efficiency was prioritized with vanilla JavaScript and optimized CSS, achieving a loading time of just 0.9 seconds.

01:28.500 --> 01:41.500
This results in performance 80% faster than the industry average, such as Biblia Online in Brazil, with near zero RAM consumption during simultaneous global access.

01:41.500 --> 01:50.500
The platform supports over 40 languages using intelligent caching to deliver static content with near zero weight anywhere in the world.

01:50.500 --> 02:03.500
The results validate the strategy. I exceeded performance benchmarks by 150% on Google PageSpeed, reaching a task completion rate of 92%.

02:03.500 --> 02:14.500
The bounce rate was reduced to 15%, while the average session duration rose to 8.5 minutes, greatly surpassing market standards.

02:14.500 --> 02:24.500
This case study demonstrates how user-centered design and scalable technical architecture can indeed transform the digital experience at scale.